OL,6,F"Especially in those early
OL,7,Fconversations, a lot of what the
OL,8,Fmedical and scientific community were
OL,9,Fadvising us at that time was not to go
OL,10,Ftoo early with the various
OL,11,Finterventions, because they were
OL,12,Fworried about public acceptance of
OL,13,Fthem," he told the inquiry.
OL,15,F"Even at that point, there was a
OL,16,Fbelief that that voluntary social
OL,17,Fdistancing together with school
OL,18,Fclosures... would be sufficient to
OL,19,Fmanage the virus.
