OL,6,FGiving more detail on the government's
OL,7,Fthinking behind the furlough scheme,
OL,8,FSunak said he faced pressure from
OL,9,Fmembers of the opposition party at the
OL,10,Ftime to keep it running longer, as
OL,11,Fwell as from "credible voices" such as
OL,12,Fthe Trades Union Congress (TUC) and
OL,13,Fthe devolved nations.
OL,15,FBut he said there was a point when
OL,16,Fkeeping the scheme running would do
OL,17,Fmore damage to the economy than
OL,18,Fstopping it, as it could artificially
OL,19,Fprop up some businesses and jobs that
OL,20,Fotherwise may not have been viable.
